<DOC><DOCNO> AP890320-0091 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-20-89 1153EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-Gotti-Threat     03-20 0262</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Gotti-Threat,0269</SECOND><HEAD>Bomb Removed From Reputed Mob Leader's Club</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Police discovered a bomb at the front door of amob hangout early today after an anonymous caller said there was a``gift'' there for John Gotti, reputed head of the Gambino organizedcrime family.   Investigators have said that Gotti and Vincent Gigante, reputedboss of another Mafia crime family, are locked in a power struggle.FBI agents have told Gotti they uncovered evidence of a plot to killhim.   Officers moved the small bomb from the steps of the Ravenitesocial club in the Little Italy section of Manhattan to a bomb squadrange in the Bronx, where it was defused. The club was empty whenthe bomb was found.   The club was the hangout of Gotti's Mafia patron, the lateAniello Dellacroce, and is one of Gotti's haunts.   Inspector Richard Mayronne said the device contained a pound ofexplosive powder.   A bomb squad detective, who spoke on the condition of anonymity,said it could have ``seriously injured anyone passing by,'' inaddition to damaging the front of the club.   A man who did not give his name telephoned the PoliceDepartment's Organized Crime Control Bureau and said, ```There is agift for John Gotti at the social club,''' according to police Sgt.Raymond O'Donnell.   Police described the bomb as a plastic box that containedbatteries wired to a circuit board with an electric timer. It wasnot clear when the timer was set to go off, police said. The powderwas contained in an aluminum bottle.</TEXT></DOC>